 simply a world of coming together (communities of people). Speeded up globalisation is 
 evened-out by increased awakeness of cultural groups and 
 communities, which is one of the main disagreements of 
 rebuilding. The idea of `global culture' advanced by Featherstone (1990) involves increased worldwide  awakeness, but 
 increased knowledge of the (quality that makes something stand alone or look different) of culture groups, 
