 p.161). 
 Errington (1997) also watches/states that opportunities 
 for (away from cities) employment are no longer the very important 
 order in keeping (groups of people/animals/things) in areas away from cities. The 
 concern of policy in areas away from cities to oppose/to go againstact (having fewer and fewer, or no, people) has to a certain extent been replaced by a 
 growing outÂ¯ux of (groups of people/animals/things) from city-based  to (away from cities) 
